docs.abstract: Savannah, Ga., is a pilgrimage destination for those interested in the abolitionist’s life, with artists interpreting his legacy in riveting shows and a film.
docs.snippet: Savannah, Ga., is a pilgrimage destination for those interested in the abolitionist’s life, with artists interpreting his legacy in riveting shows and a film.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAVANNAH, Ga. — Frederick Douglass passed through this elegant Southern city only once, for the briefest of visits — a half-hour whistle-stop on his rail journey to a speaking engagement in Jacksonville, Fla.

headline.main: Looking for Frederick Douglass in Savannah

docs.abstract: The pro-democracy camp’s stunning victory in citywide district elections means a younger class of political neophytes will soon take office.
docs.snippet: The pro-democracy camp’s stunning victory in citywide district elections means a younger class of political neophytes will soon take office.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Hong Kong’s district council election saw the pro-establishment camp have one of its biggest defeats since the territory returned to Chinese control 22 years ago, as dozens of seasoned politicians were replaced with a crop of newcomers, many of whom were inspired to run by the antigovernment protests.

headline.main: Meet 5 of Hong Kong’s Newest Politicians

docs.abstract: Two chains canceled future screenings of “Blue Story” after incidents this weekend. Critics accused the chains of being “cowardly” and “racist,” but the theaters said they were worried about safety.

headline.main: British Movie Theaters Pull Gang Film After Violence at Screenings

docs.abstract: A surge in voting, especially by young people, allowed democracy advocates to win many more seats on local councils.
docs.snippet: A surge in voting, especially by young people, allowed democracy advocates to win many more seats on local councils.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Pro-democracy candidates buoyed by months of street protests in Hong Kong won a stunning victory in local elections on Sunday, as record numbers voted in a vivid expression of the city’s aspirations and its anger with the Chinese government.

headline.main: Hong Kong Election Results Give Democracy Backers Big Win
headline.print_headline: In Hong Kong, A Banner Day For Democracy

docs.abstract: The film, about a jaded veteran officer and his rookie partner, plays like an amalgam of the tropes of numerous TV and movie police procedurals.
docs.snippet: The film, about a jaded veteran officer and his rookie partner, plays like an amalgam of the tropes of numerous TV and movie police procedurals.
docs.lead_paragraph: “Crown Vic” begins in the midst of a kinetic shootout, the camera zipping back and forth as a pair of masked robbers careen away from the L.A.P.D. in a car. But the writer-director Joel Souza soon dissipates the adrenaline rush of this opening into a verbose, hackneyed thriller about a night in the lives of a veteran patrol officer and his trainee.

headline.main: ‘Crown Vic’ Review: A Cop Thriller Abounding in Cliché

docs.abstract: After initially saying the 19-year-old had lunged at the police with a weapon, the authorities later charged an officer with murder and opened an investigation.

docs.lead_paragraph: SYDNEY, Australia — Thousands of Australians have taken to the streets this week to protest the police killing of an Aboriginal teenager in a remote community, a case that has added fuel to long-simmering anger over the government’s behavior toward the country’s Indigenous people.

headline.main: ‘We’re Just So Angry’: Australians Protest Police Killing of Aboriginal Teenager
headline.print_headline: Police Killing  Of Teenager Stirs Protests In Australia
